Project: Unveiling the Determinants of Psychological Intimate Partner Violence (IPV) Against Mothers in Mexico - Insights from Model-Based Boosting
Author: Clara Strasser Ceballos
Date: October 12, 2023

=== File Structure ===

- src: This folder contains all files used in the main analysis.
        - data: the main data set and the robustness data set is generated. 
        - descriptives:
            - imputed_pmm_m1: contains descriptives for the main data set
            - non_imputed2: contains descriptives for robustness data set 
        - main_analysis: conducts the estimation and creates the final data set
            - formula: model 1 is specified.
            - main: estimation.
            - add_geo: add long and lat to the data set. Attention: final data set is generated here!
            - inspection: unique values and missings are tested before estimation.
        - robustness: gam() and glm() are conducted instead of mboost()
        - robustness2: the same analysis as in main_analysis is conducted but with non-imputed data.
        - extension: EFA and CFA is conducted. Two data sets are generated for the alternative outcomes. The estimation is conducted on each generated outcome.
        - plots: the plots are generated e.g for the boosting iterations etc.
        
- results: This folder contains some results of the main analysis.
        - plots: Plots generated with the main data set (imputed missing values).
        - plots_robustness2: Plots generated with the robustness data set (no imputed missing values).
        
- renv: This folder contains all r-packages used in the project, as well as their correct version.

- functions: This folder contains the functions used in the project.
  - partial_effects()
  - propplot()
  - conf_table()
  - fa_table()
  
- data: Contains the relevant data
  - endireh_2021:
  - final_data: contains the main data set (data_imp_pmm_m1) and robustnes data set (data_no_imp2)
  - ipv: contains info on the outcome variable.
  - prep_data: data after preparation steps of the main data set.
  - prep_data_robustness2: data after preparation steps of the robustness data set.
  - risk_factors: contains at each level of the ecological model the constructed variables.

- README: contains overall information on the project.



